    <refsection id="Description_MMR_IdealGearR2T">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block is a gearbox transforming rotational into translational motion (rack and pignon system) with bearings, with:
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>
                \begin{eqnarray}
                ratio = \frac{\Large{\varphi_a - \varphi_{bearingR}}}{\Large{s_b - s_{bearingT}}}
                \end{eqnarray}
            </latex>
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>\varphi_a</latex> (resp. <latex>s_b</latex>) is the angular position (resp. the position) of the pignon (resp. the rack), and
            <latex>\varphi_{bearingR}</latex> (resp. <latex>s_{bearingT}</latex>) is the bearing of rotational motion (resp. translational motion).
        </para>
    </refsection>
